miscConds.notes: Cash bail applied to Costs. Balance to be paid as a condition of probation.
Comply with Mental Health evaluation and treatment deemed appropriate. Attend at least 2 Self Help meetings per week.

Submit to an AODA assessment, follow through with any treatment, counseling.  No use or possession of alcohol or illegal drugs/drug paraphernalia. Comply with random urine screens.  Maintain absolute sobriety. No use or possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription. Valid prescriptions only with prior agent approval and to be taken only in the manner they are prescribed.

Upon Petition - Court will consider early termination of probation at any point after 6 months, if all conditions are met and agent deems appropriate. 
No Violent contact with victims listed in the criminal complaint. 
Maintain employment and/or school combination. Follow through with any assessments, evaluations, treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent. 
No association with any known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged or distributed. 
*No presence on any premises whose primary business is serving or selling alcohol (i.e bars, taverns, or liquor stores). 
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 
If Probation/Extended Supervision is revoked and/or a prison term ordered, outstanding financial obligations shall be collected pursuant to statutory provisions, including deductions from inmate prison monies.  If discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and government entities for outstanding financial obligations.  Collections may include income assignment.

8:47 AM Defendant Christopher M Paulino in court.  Attorney Tyler A Jochman in court for Christopher M Paulino. District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Jack Rieder. Victim rights have been complied with by the Waukesha County District Attorneys Office. 

Defense requests to proceed to plea/sentencing today. State files amended information. 

Defendant enters a no-contest plea to count #1 and count #2 of the amended information. Court conducts colloquy with the Defendant and finds them guilty of count #1 and count#2 of the amended information. 

State makes sentencing arguments. Defense makes sentencing arguments. Defendant makes statements. 

Court orders the following:

COUNT #1:
SENTENCE WITHHELD.

Term of Probation: 12 MONTHS

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
Follow through with any assessments, evaluations, treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent; 
Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
No violent contact with: victims listed in criminal complaint
DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed.
No presence on any premises whose primary business is serving or selling alcohol (i.e bars, taverns, or liquor stores).
Attend at least 2 self help meetings per week. 
Mental Heath evaluation and treatment deemed appropriate.
Upon Petition - Court will consider early termination of probation at any point after 6 months, if all conditions are met and agent deems appropriate. 

COSTS:  $243.00
DV SURCHARGE: $100.00
DNA SAMPLE AND SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
Cash bond to be applied to costs. 

COUNT #2:
SENTENCE WITHHELD.

Term of Probation: 12 MONTHS
Concurrent to: Count #1

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
Same as count #1

COSTS:  $243.00
DV SURCHARGE: $100.00
DNA SAMPLE AND SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
Cash bond to be applied to costs, balance to be paid as a condition of probation. 

6 days jail credit toward any sentence imposed

Appeal rights given.
